for subdir in subdirectories: # first test dir
    files = os.listdir(subdir)
    print(files)
    os.chdir(subdir)
    print(os.getcwd())
    images = []
    for file in files:
        image = cv2.imread(file, 0)
        image = utils.delete_description(image, utils.get_size_for_crop(image))
        images.append(image)
    os.chdir('..')

    # plot original images
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5)
    for i in range(len(images)):
        axes[i].imshow(images[i], cmap='gray')
        axes[i].set_title(f'Image{i+1} original')
    fig.set_size_inches(20, 10)

    # plot masks
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5)
    for i in range(len(images)):
        image_mask = get_cells(images[i], 'Ellipse detect')
        axes[i].imshow(image_mask, cmap='gray')
        axes[i].set_title(f'Image{i+1} binary mask')
    fig.set_size_inches(20, 10)
